- An unemployment rate below 5% is often considered to be very low, indicating a 'booming' economy; 
- Population growth rate is a key indicator of economic health; 
- Median age is an important demographic statistic, often used to analyze age-related trends; 
- Age distribution provides further insights into the demographic structure of the county; 
- GDP is a common measure of economic activity; 
- Change in growth rate and change in population are useful metrics to track economic development over time.
